text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia lanuginophylla, or woolly wattle, is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The dense shrub typically grows to a height of 0.5 to 1.2 metres (2 to 4 ft). It blooms from July to October and produces yellow flowers.
